    "about": "Building the \"Asymmetric Response\" in AI: Efficiency over Brute Force.\n\nWhile the world burns billions on GPU clusters to scale Transformers, I focus on the next generation of AI architectures: Mamba (SSM), Quantum-Inspired Tensor Networks, RWKV, and Liquid Neural Networks (LNN). My goal is not just to wrap GPT APIs, but to build sovereign, energy-efficient, and mathematically robust AGI systems.\n\nMy philosophy is Neuro-Symbolic AGI:\nAGI = LNN (Logic/Physics/Causality) + LLM (World Knowledge) + QML (Quantum Speed)\nI am a Product-Driven CTO with 12+ years of P&L ownership, turning complex DeepTech concepts into profitable vertical platforms.\n\nMy \"Secret Arsenal\" & Projects:\n🚀 Muhaddis AI (Islamic Intelligence):\nTech: Utilizing Mamba/SSM architectures for infinite context processing without the quadratic cost of Transformers.\nMission: Precise Sanad/Matn analysis and source tracing where \"hallucinations\" are not an option.\n\n🧬 Pharmacy AI & Shafa AI (MedTech):\nTech: Neuro-symbolic engines combined with Knowledge Graphs.\nMission: Clinical decision support where logic \n\n(System 2) must override probability (System 1).\nmining Minerals AI (Industrial):\nTech: Liquid Neural Networks (LNN) and Quantum-Inspired algorithms.\n\nMission: Adapting to chaos. Managing exploration risks and industrial optimization in dynamic, real-world physical environments.\nCore Competencies:\nPost-Transformer Architectures: State Space Models (Mamba), Linear Attention (RWKV), ODE-based Networks (LNN).\n\nSovereign AI: Edge computing, offline-first models, and data privacy.\nFull-Stack AI: From training 700B+ models to multi-agent orchestration and RAG.\nI don't just predict the future of AI. I engineer it.",
